title: Print - cash balance reports from other days
text: If the shop assistant has done the cash balance report in the evening, but it didn't print, they can repeat the print of the receipt in the POS: Shortcuts->Search Note Choose "Dato interval"->Start day: Day of the cash balance they want to print. Slut date: The following day->Search Now check the following: What is the receipt number of the last receipt of the start date you selected? What is the receipt number of the first receipt of the slut date you selected? The receipt of the cash balance you are looking is not visible in this overview and has the receipt number that lies between these two receipts, in our example receipt number 650. Make a note of this number. Click on "Indtast Bonnummer" in the top left-hand corner->enter the receipt number->click on the green tick->Click on "Bon kopi" Alternatively, they can print a cash balance report: or by opening the Windows Explorer and going to c:\\POS\Reports. Sort by date modified and locate the latest report, open and print.
description:
If the shop assistant has done the cash balance report in the evening, but it didn't print, they can repeat the print of the receipt in the POS:

Shortcuts->Search Note



Choose "Dato interval"->Start day: Day of the cash balance they want to print. Slut date: The following day->Search

Now check the following:

What is the receipt number of the last receipt of the start date you selected?

What is the receipt number of the first receipt of the slut date you selected?


The receipt of the cash balance you are looking is not visible in this overview and has the receipt number that lies between these two receipts, in our example receipt number 650. Make a note of this number.
Click on "Indtast Bonnummer" in the top left-hand corner->enter the receipt number->click on the green tick->Click on "Bon kopi"



Alternatively, they can print a cash balance report:

  
 

or by opening the Windows Explorer and going to c:\\POS\Reports. Sort by date modified and locate the latest report, open and print.

title: Print – Order Transaction Report
text: Order transaction reports give access to Sales lines (what was sold on the chosen date(s)) Item purchase (what was bought on the chosen date(s)) This includes returns. Item Transfers (what was transfered to another shop on the chosen date(s)). Old reports can be found in the following folders on the PC: RIAB – C:/POS/Reports POS – C:/Downloads/SAClient/download Order Transaction Report
description:
Order transaction reports give access to  

  

Sales lines (what was sold on the chosen date(s)) 

  

Item purchase (what was bought on the chosen date(s)) This includes returns. 

  

Item Transfers (what was transfered to another shop on the chosen date(s)). 

  

Old reports can be found in the following folders on the PC:  

  

RIAB – C:/POS/Reports 

 

  

POS – C:/Downloads/SAClient/download 

 

  

  

Order Transaction Report

title: Print - reports (Financial/Employe/Sales etc.)
text: Dansk: Åben POS -> Genveje -> Rapporter Sæt dato interval og klik på den rapport du skal bruge. HUSK!!! Rapporter udkskrives på bonprinter med det samme. Hvis du ikke vil printe på bonprinteren, husk at sætte hak i Udskriv journal på skærm English: Open POS -> Shortcuts -> Reports Choose the dates and click on the report you want to print. ATTENTION!!! All reports are printed on the receipt printer immediately. If you do not want a printout, remember to tick Print Journal to screen first. Deutsch: POS öffnen -> erw. Funktionen -> Berichte Datum wählen und den beliebigen Bericht anklicken ACHTUNG!!! Alle Berichte werden sofort auf dem Belegdrucker ausgedruckt. Wenn Sie den Bericht nicht ausdrucken wollen, dann setzen Sie zuerst einen Harken in Drucken Journal auf dem Bildschirm
description:
Dansk: 

  

Åben POS -> Genveje -> Rapporter 

 

  

Sæt dato interval og klik på den rapport du skal bruge.  

  

HUSK!!! Rapporter udkskrives på bonprinter med det samme. Hvis du ikke vil printe på bonprinteren, husk at sætte hak i Udskriv journal på skærm 

  

 

  

English: 

  

Open POS -> Shortcuts -> Reports 

 

  

Choose the dates and click on the report you want to print. 

  

ATTENTION!!! All reports are printed on the receipt printer immediately. If you do not want a printout, remember to tick Print Journal to screen first. 

  

 

  

Deutsch: 

  

POS öffnen -> erw. Funktionen -> Berichte 

 

  

Datum wählen und den beliebigen Bericht anklicken 

  

ACHTUNG!!! Alle Berichte werden sofort auf dem Belegdrucker ausgedruckt. Wenn Sie den Bericht nicht ausdrucken wollen, dann setzen Sie zuerst einen Harken in Drucken Journal auf dem Bildschirm

title: RIAB POS can not create Print outs
text: If the customer wants to create Print outs and they do not appear here: It might be related to the settings in Back Office: Client info->Miscellaneous->Client is "user report recipients" If the box is ticked, print outs only can be created in the POS. If the box is not ticked, print outs only can be created in Back Office. !!!Attention: This only applies to RIAB cash registers!!!
description:
If the customer wants to create Print outs and they do not appear here:
It might be related to the settings in Back Office:
Client info->Miscellaneous->Client is "user report recipients"

If the box is ticked, print outs only can be created in the POS.


If the box is not ticked, print outs only can be created in Back Office.

!!!Attention: This only applies to RIAB cash registers!!!

title: No response from printer when printing from POS
text: If nothing happens when trying to print a report directly from DDDPOS, you need to check the printer/printer settings. Check the cables/wireless connection Make sure the printer is on, has paper, and is running as intended. From windows printer settings, check if a test page can be printed. If all of the above checks out, check if the default printer in windows is set to the correct printer. Occasionally when a new printer is set up, this can be an issue, as the print will be sent to the no longer connected printer
description:
If nothing happens when trying to print a report directly from DDDPOS, you need to check the printer/printer settings. 


Check the cables/wireless connection


Make sure the printer is on, has paper, and is running as intended. 


From windows printer settings, check if a test page can be printed. 


If all of the above checks out, check if the default printer in windows is set to the correct printer. Occasionally when a new printer is set up, this can be an issue, as the print will be sent to the no longer connected printer
